---
import DocsLayout from '../../layouts/DocsLayout.astro'
const headings = [{ id: 'everyday', label: 'Everyday commands' }, { id: 'presets', label: 'Prompt presets' }, { id: 'maintenance', label: 'Maintenance' }]
---
<DocsLayout title="CLI reference" description="Manage prompt presets, terminal colors, updates, health checks, and the installed Santi020k configuration." path="/docs/cli/" {headings}>
  <section id="everyday"><h2>Everyday commands</h2><dl class="docs-command-list"><div><dt><code>santi020k-terminal status</code></dt><dd>Show the installed version, configuration schema, active preset, and managed paths.</dd></div><div><dt><code>santi020k-terminal update</code></dt><dd>Update the package and refresh managed configuration.</dd></div><div><dt><code>santi020k-terminal doctor</code></dt><dd>Inspect dependencies, configuration, and managed state without changing anything.</dd></div><div><dt><code>santi020k-terminal doctor --fix</code></dt><dd>Review and confirm repairs for missing tools or configuration.</dd></div></dl></section>
  <section id="presets"><h2>Prompt presets and colors</h2><dl class="docs-command-list"><div><dt><code>santi020k-terminal preset use rich</code></dt><dd>Use the complete icon-based Powerline prompt.</dd></div><div><dt><code>santi020k-terminal preset use portable</code></dt><dd>Replace application icons with readable labels.</dd></div><div><dt><code>santi020k-terminal preset use minimal</code></dt><dd>Remove runtime modules for a quieter prompt.</dd></div><div><dt><code>santi020k-terminal colors install</code></dt><dd>Import iTerm2 colors or install packaged Ghostty, Kitty, and Alacritty themes.</dd></div></dl></section>
  <section id="maintenance"><h2>Removal and recovery</h2><p>Run <code>santi020k-terminal uninstall</code> to remove the managed shell integration. Homebrew remains responsible for uninstalling the formula and its dependencies.</p><aside class="docs-callout"><b>Inspect before repairing</b><p>Start with <code>doctor</code>. Add <code>--fix</code> only after reviewing the reported state and proposed repairs.</p></aside></section>
</DocsLayout>
